content: The game graphics are so ugly I wasted my money

Unplayable unless you plan to play by only controlling movement & when to shot (do not turn off automatic aim). BETTER OFFLINE TANK GAMES: Infinite Tanks also by Atypical Games (~3GB, you can get involved in the action & has UI customization); more realistic, World Of Steel by BraveTale (~100MB, need an average or above tablet - heavy processor uses, citadel type defense armour, great physics), & Tanktastic 3D tanks by Roman B. (~600MB, very hard to get started in, more an online game).

I'm disappointed. This could have been a great single player tank battle game if the devs had just stuck to their guns. The plane, car and boat sections ruin the game because they just don't feel good to handle. There should be separate control options for the plane because it's literally unplayable with the gyro. The tank upgrades are useless because you can't use them in the campaign. Also the reloading time for the tank cannon is longer than it should, making the shooting a complete grind.
